<subSubSection id="C30DBD81FFEFFFE9FF74F958CED7FE50" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="274" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA8EE0AFFEFFFE9FF74F958CED7FE50" blockId="2.[151,1436,1761,2038]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="274" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis id="B9633218FFEFFFE8FF74F958CC56F906" bold="true" box="[151,267,1761,1786]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Remarks.</emphasis>
Kilburn (
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEFFFE8FE9BF95BCCEEF906" box="[376,435,1762,1786]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" value="1988.0">1988</number>
) remarked the close resemblance in shell characters of members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C179589FFEFFFE8FB48F958C8C1F906" authority="Oliver, 1915" authorityName="Oliver" authorityYear="1915" box="[1195,1436,1761,1786]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Iredalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9633218FFEFFFE8FB48F958C854F906" box="[1195,1289,1761,1786]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Iredalea</emphasis>
Oliver, 
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEFFFE8FA87F958C8C1F906" box="[1380,1436,1761,1786]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" value="1915.0">1915</number>
</taxonomicName>
and the monotypic 
<taxonomicName id="4C179589FFEFFFE8FE9AF8BCCFA8F8E2" authority="Monterosato, 1884" authorityName="Monterosato" authorityYear="1884" box="[377,757,1797,1822]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Crassopleura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9633218FFEFFFE8FE9AF8BCCF4FF8E2" box="[377,530,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Crassopleura</emphasis>
Monterosato, 
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEFFFE8FD58F8BFCFA8F8E2" box="[699,757,1798,1822]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" value="1884.0">1884</number>
</taxonomicName>
, based on 
<taxonomicName id="4C179589FFEFFFE8FC96F8BCC87CF8E2" authority="Bivona Ant." authorityName="Bivona Ant." box="[885,1313,1797,1822]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Pleurotoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="maravignae">
<emphasis id="B9633218FFEFFFE8FC96F8BCC9D4F8E1" box="[885,1161,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Pleurotoma maravignae</emphasis>
Bivona Ant.
</taxonomicName>
in Bivona And., 
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEFFFE8FF00F893CC46F8BE" box="[227,283,1834,1858]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" value="1838.0">1838</number>
from the eastern Atlantic to the Mediterranean Sea, but suggested that the two genera can be distinguished on the basis of radular features. More recently Scarponi &amp; Della Bella (
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEFFFE8FB6AF8F7C99BF89A" box="[1161,1222,1870,1894]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" value="2004.0">2004</number>
), while discussing 
<taxonomicName id="4C179589FFEFFFE8FF74F8C8CCE3F875" box="[151,446,1905,1930]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Crassopleura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="maravignae">
<emphasis id="B9633218FFEFFFE8FF74F8C8CCE3F875" box="[151,446,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Crassopleura maravignae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, noted that two forms of this species can be recognized on the basis of the number of axial ribs, namely a Pliocene form bearing 
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEFFFE8FD6DF82FCF88F852" box="[654,725,1942,1966]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" value="16.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="14.0">14–18</number>
axial ribs on the last whorl and a Pleistocene one with more numerous ribs (
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEFFFE8FEB0F800CCC3F82E" box="[339,414,1977,2002]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" value="23.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="21.0">21–25</number>
). The authors also remarked that the parietal pad of 
<taxonomicName id="4C179589FFEFFFE8FBC6F803C98FF82D" box="[1061,1234,1978,2001]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Crassopleura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="maravignae">
<emphasis id="B9633218FFEFFFE8FBC6F803C98FF82D" box="[1061,1234,1978,2001]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">C. maravignae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
tends to form a moderately deep, narrow and posteriorly directed spout with the end of the outer lip. According to Scarponi &amp; Della Bella (
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEEFFE9FECAFF21CC39FF4C" box="[297,356,152,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" value="2004.0">2004</number>
) this feature, not observed in members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C179589FFEEFFE9FCB2FF2ECEF2FF4C" box="[849,943,151,176]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Iredalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9633218FFEEFFE9FCB2FF2ECEF2FF4C" box="[849,943,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="274">Iredalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, supports recognition of 
<taxonomicName id="4C179589FFEEFFE9FB31FF2EC836FF4C" box="[1234,1387,151,176]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Crassopleura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9633218FFEEFFE9FB31FF2EC836FF4C" box="[1234,1387,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="274">Crassopleura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C179589FFEEFFE9FF74FF05CDA8FF29" box="[151,245,188,213]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Iredalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9633218FFEEFFE9FF74FF05CDA8FF29" box="[151,245,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="274">Iredalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as distinct genera. However, in the Pliocene specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C179589FFEEFFE9FC6AFF04C96CFF28" box="[905,1073,189,212]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Crassopleura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="maravignae">
<emphasis id="B9633218FFEEFFE9FC6AFF04C96CFF28" box="[905,1073,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="274">C. maravignae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Scarponi &amp; Della Bella, 
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEEFFE9FABFFF05C8C5FF28" box="[1372,1432,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" value="2004.0">2004</number>
: plate 
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEEFFE9FF36FF59CDBEFF04" box="[213,227,224,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" value="1.0">1</number>
, fig. 
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEEFFE9FEFCFF59CC72FF04" box="[287,303,224,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" value="2.0">2</number>
), the posterior spout is rather weak or even absent as in the recent specimens figured in the WoRMS register (Appeltans 
<emphasis id="B9633218FFEEFFE9FE9AFEBCCCE9FEE1" box="[377,436,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="274">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEEFFE9FE27FEBDCCA3FEE0" box="[452,510,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" value="2012.0">2012</number>
) (accessed at http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&amp;id= 
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEEFFE9FADFFEBDC8CCFEE1" box="[1340,1425,260,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" value="139659.0">139659</number>
). Thus, this stated difference is, in our opinion, of very doubtful value. In this paper 
<taxonomicName id="4C179589FFEEFFE9FBA8FE9EC9F4FEBC" box="[1099,1193,295,320]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Iredalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9633218FFEEFFE9FBA8FE9EC9F4FEBC" box="[1099,1193,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="274">Iredalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is retained as a valid genus in accord with Kilburn (
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEEFFE9FE08FEF5CF75FE98" box="[491,552,332,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" value="1988.0">1988</number>
). In addition to the Recent species revised by Kilburn (
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEEFFE9FB6FFEF5C99AFE98" box="[1164,1223,332,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" value="1988.0">1988</number>
) and recognized in the WoRMS register, Scarponi &amp; Della Bella (
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEEFFE9FD79FEC9CF8AFE74" box="[666,727,368,392]" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" value="2004.0">2004</number>
: 
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEEFFE9FD02FEC9CFA3FE74" box="[737,766,368,392]" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" value="24.0">24</number>
) recognized 
<taxonomicName id="4C179589FFEEFFE9FC6DFED6C8C1FE74" authority="Cipolla, 1914" authorityName="Cipolla" authorityYear="1914" box="[910,1436,367,392]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Drillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="stoppanii" subGenus="Cymatosyrinx">
<emphasis id="B9633218FFEEFFE9FC6DFED6C9A0FE74" box="[910,1277,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="274">Drillia (Cymatosyrinx) stoppanii</emphasis>
Cipolla, 
<number id="3DDFFC2DFFEEFFE9FA87FEC9C8C1FE74" box="[1380,1436,368,392]" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" value="1914.0">1914</number>
</taxonomicName>
from the Pliocene of 
<collectingCountry id="F300AE9AFFEEFFE9FE60FE2DCCEBFE51" box="[387,438,404,429]" name="Italy" pageId="3" pageNumber="274">Italy</collectingCountry>
as a fossil member of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C179589FFEEFFE9FCC6FE2DCEDEFE51" box="[805,899,404,429]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Iredalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="274" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9633218FFEEFFE9FCC6FE2DCEDEFE51" box="[805,899,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="274">Iredalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
